different states, you might have

98
00:03:59,138 --> 00:04:02,026
to rely on things like Skype
to use video conferencing,

99
00:04:02,026 --> 00:04:04,718
or you may have to just use E-mails.

100
00:04:04,718 --> 00:04:06,688
These are things you're going
to have to consider as part

101
00:04:06,688 --> 00:04:07,818
of your project.

102
00:04:07,818 --> 00:04:10,219
Sometimes you need a
high level of formality.

103
00:04:10,219 --> 00:04:11,968
If you're going to be putting
up a report, for instance,

104
00:04:11,968 --> 00:04:14,562
that would be in written
form, not face-to-face

105
00:04:14,562 --> 00:04:15,922
communication.

106
00:04:15,922 --> 00:04:19,429
Written word does have it's
place, but there are a lot

107
00:04:19,429 --> 00:04:22,120
of disadvantages when
dealing with written word.

108
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:24,002
Have you ever gotten a text
message from somebody and

109
00:04:24,002 --> 00:04:26,810
you're not exactly sure if
they were joking or not?

110
00:04:26,810 --> 00:04:28,668
Well if they had told you
that face-to-face, you

111
00:04:28,668 --> 00:04:29,912
would've known, right?

112
00:04:29,912 --> 00:04:31,312
Because you can read the body language.

113
00:04:31,312 --> 00:04:33,584
And this is one of those
drawbacks from written word

114
00:04:33,584 --> 00:04:34,417
to verbal.

115
00:04:35,378 --> 00:04:37,758
Your project manager or your
team manager is going to be

116
00:04:37,758 --> 00:04:41,062
responsible and aware of
how this team is going to be

117
00:04:41,062 --> 00:04:42,141
communicating.

118
00:04:42,141 --> 00:04:44,403
It's their responsibility
to come up with a good

119
00:04:44,403 --> 00:04:48,080
communication plan and help
encourage the team to use it.

120
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:51,039
Communication does need to
be organized and it does

121
00:04:51,039 --> 00:04:52,392
need to be planned.

122
00:04:52,392 --> 00:04:54,514
One of the ways that we do
that is our daily stand-up

123
00:04:54,514 --> 00:04:56,880
meetings as part of
our Scrum cycle, right?

124
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:59,795
Every morning we stand up
and for 15 minutes we go over

125
00:04:59,795 --> 00:05:02,588
what we did yesterday and
what we're going to do today.

126
00:05:02,588 --> 00:05:05,127
That's part of rich
communication, and again when that

127
00:05:05,127 --> 00:05:07,941
can occur face-to-face that
is going to be the best way

128
00:05:07,941 --> 00:05:09,506
of doing it.

129
00:05:09,506 --> 00:05:11,626
One of the questions I
often get asked when people

130
00:05:11,626 --> 00:05:14,605
start working an Agile
environment is: "How should I

131
00:05:14,605 --> 00:05:17,793
communicate?", and I will
tell you that I am a big fan

132
00:05:17,793 --> 00:05:20,978
of face-to-face communication
and using a lot of

133
00:05:20,978 --> 00:05:22,317
visualization.

134
00:05:22,317 --> 00:05:24,395
Because if I can draw
something up on the board, it's

135
00:05:24,395 --> 00:05:27,706
going to be a lot clearer
than if we use a lot of words,

136
00:05:27,706 --> 00:05:31,187
and so a three-page E-mail
is not nearly as effective

137
00:05:31,187 --> 00:05:33,543
as a one-page infographic.

138
00:05:33,543 --> 00:05:35,811
So that's the idea here
with visualization and then,

139
00:05:35,811 --> 00:05:38,411
if I can do that in a face-to-face
manner, that's going to

140
00:05:38,411 --> 00:05:40,574
eliminate a lot of
those questions as well.

141
00:05:40,574 --> 00:05:43,918
So for the exam, remember
lots of visualization, lots

142
00:05:43,918 --> 00:05:45,190
of face-to-face.

143
00:05:45,190 --> 00:05:46,868
These are good things when
you're trying to communicate

144
00:05:46,868 --> 00:05:47,865
effectively.



